item.title: 'How Iraq mistakes fueled ISIS rise'
item.description: Addressing the nation from the Oval office on Sunday night, President Barack Obama outlined the current U.S. approach to fighting the Islamic State of Iraq and Syria (ISIS). Obama stated that we have been at war with Islamist terrorists since 9/11. However, the number of terrorists has proliferated since then in large part as the unintended consequences of policies the United States has pursued.
